Question: Do you think standard tests accurately assess student abilities?
Answer:
depends on the criteria on the test. if the test is concerned more with theoretical concepts and trivial what if scenarios , then no, it is not an accurate assessment of anything other than the amount of free time a proffesor has on their hands. if the test concerns practical application of the material and effectively covers topics covered in class and not asspulls from a professors day of  pondering a subject then yes